WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.009 --> 00:00:11.052
Start from the beginning.

2
00:00:12.179 --> 00:00:14.431
<i>Nothing could have prepared us
for what lay waiting.</i>

3
00:00:17.810 --> 00:00:20.163
<i>Flint's powers must have come
from the same place.</i>

4
00:00:20.187 --> 00:00:22.791
<i>I'm Mr. Byrne. Mayor Morris forgot</i>

5
00:00:22.815 --> 00:00:24.710
<i>who runs this town.</i>

6
00:00:24.734 --> 00:00:26.670
- Four veterans from the POW camp.
- All seen

7
00:00:26.694 --> 00:00:28.213
Dr. Alethea Faber.

8
00:00:28.237 --> 00:00:29.923
Well. what the hell are we waiting for?

9
00:00:29.947 --> 00:00:31.800
There's a reporter asking
to speak with you.

10
00:00:31.824 --> 00:00:33.969
<i>This is my secretary Ogden.</i>

11
00:00:33.993 --> 00:00:36.304
<i>You really had no idea</i>

12
00:00:36.328 --> 00:00:37.973
your patients have superpowers?

13
00:00:37.997 --> 00:00:39.057
Are you calling her

14
00:00:39.081 --> 00:00:40.183
a liar?

15
00:00:40.207 --> 00:00:41.893
I am sorry. I cannot help you.

16
00:00:41.917 --> 00:00:43.145
<i>Faber's been looking</i>

17
00:00:43.169 --> 00:00:45.313
for a cure. but she's just gonna kill him.

18
00:00:45.337 --> 00:00:47.023
Let me tell Cat before you print it.

19
00:00:47.047 --> 00:00:48.108
I'll give you a day.

20
00:00:48.132 --> 00:00:49.901
<i>Flint's gonna die?</i>

21
00:00:49.925 --> 00:00:53.530
What's left for us? What if we went
someplace where nobody knows us?

22
00:00:53.554 --> 00:00:55.365
<i>I'm willing to take a chance and find out.</i>

23
00:00:55.389 --> 00:00:57.701
If that reporter publishes.
they're coming for us.

24
00:00:57.725 --> 00:01:00.537
Dr. Faber.
are you really able to help them?

25
00:01:00.561 --> 00:01:02.289
You know who The Spider is. don't you?

26
00:01:02.313 --> 00:01:04.147
Ben Reilly.

27
00:02:30.276 --> 00:02:32.610
What the hell?

28
00:02:33.904 --> 00:02:35.340
Mr. Reilly.

29
00:02:35.364 --> 00:02:37.592
I-I'm not here to cause any trouble.

30
00:02:37.616 --> 00:02:40.911
I-I'd just like
a minute of your time. please.

31
00:02:41.996 --> 00:02:43.223
That's...

32
00:02:43.247 --> 00:02:46.017
That's not really necessary.

33
00:02:46.041 --> 00:02:48.687
I haven't had a gun in my hand
since the war.

34
00:02:48.711 --> 00:02:49.794
Civil War?

35
00:02:53.257 --> 00:02:54.860
You don't remember me.

36
00:02:54.884 --> 00:02:56.319
From yesterday.

37
00:02:56.343 --> 00:02:58.363
No. Back in France.

38
00:02:58.387 --> 00:03:00.448
You saved my life.

39
00:03:00.472 --> 00:03:02.391
What are you talking about?

40
00:03:03.726 --> 00:03:05.311
Easy. old man.

41
00:03:08.939 --> 00:03:10.834
They called me "Freckles"

42
00:03:10.858 --> 00:03:13.003
because I looked so young.

43
00:03:13.027 --> 00:03:16.697
They thought I was 15
and lied to get in the war.

44
00:03:17.281 --> 00:03:21.052
I suppose I was one
of the f-fortunate ones.

45
00:03:21.076 --> 00:03:23.096
I'm still breathing. but my mutation

46
00:03:23.120 --> 00:03:26.057
is aging me at a dog's clip

47
00:03:26.081 --> 00:03:28.792
and getting worse as it goes.

48
00:03:29.293 --> 00:03:34.357
Dr. Faber is my last chance to survive.

49
00:03:34.381 --> 00:03:36.467
She's a good woman.

50
00:03:36.967 --> 00:03:38.886
Trying to do a good thing.

51
00:03:41.972 --> 00:03:43.641
Want a drink?

52
00:03:48.562 --> 00:03:52.208
How old are you really?

53
00:03:52.232 --> 00:03:54.419
I'll be 36 in April.

54
00:03:54.443 --> 00:03:56.320
If I live to see it.

55
00:03:56.946 --> 00:03:59.257
I'm not the only one who's suffering.

56
00:03:59.281 --> 00:04:01.009
- Th-That's why I came here.
- If you're looking

57
00:04:01.033 --> 00:04:02.761
for the files. I don't have 'em.

58
00:04:02.785 --> 00:04:04.304
The files don't matter.

59
00:04:04.328 --> 00:04:07.891
I mean. not really.
They're just a laundry list of failures.

60
00:04:07.915 --> 00:04:10.459
D-Dead ends and dashed hopes.

61
00:04:11.043 --> 00:04:12.503
It's your reporter friend.

62
00:04:13.087 --> 00:04:15.065
If he prints that story.

63
00:04:15.089 --> 00:04:17.800
that's the end of Faber's work.

64
00:04:18.801 --> 00:04:20.426
That's the end of me.

65
00:04:22.137 --> 00:04:24.055
I'm sorry.

66
00:04:25.349 --> 00:04:26.868
But it's too late.

67
00:04:26.892 --> 00:04:30.121
Robbie wouldn't stop
even if I asked him to.

68
00:04:30.145 --> 00:04:32.773
And you-you won't even try?

69
00:04:33.440 --> 00:04:34.501
No.

70
00:04:34.525 --> 00:04:36.211
Why?

71
00:04:36.235 --> 00:04:39.863
I mean. don't-don't you want to see
your comrades cured?

72
00:04:40.572 --> 00:04:42.657
Would you want to be cured?

73
00:04:43.867 --> 00:04:45.512
What is that supposed to mean?

74
00:04:45.536 --> 00:04:47.847
Means I know who

75
00:04:47.871 --> 00:04:49.557
and what you really are.

76
00:04:49.581 --> 00:04:54.896
I followed you into that ward
that day when you and your unit saved us.

77
00:04:54.920 --> 00:04:57.399
That day when that thing...

78
00:04:57.423 --> 00:04:58.650
bit you.

79
00:04:58.674 --> 00:05:00.610
If you hadn't changed your name.

80
00:05:00.634 --> 00:05:04.263
I would have come knocking
at your door years ago.

81
00:05:06.682 --> 00:05:08.350
Dementia hit early?

82
00:05:09.018 --> 00:05:10.227
Don't do that.

83
00:05:10.894 --> 00:05:13.623
I can excuse a lot.
but I deserve better than that.

84
00:05:13.647 --> 00:05:17.293
You're delivering me a death sentence.

85
00:05:17.317 --> 00:05:19.945
At least have the decency to be honest.

86
00:05:30.456 --> 00:05:34.227
Truth is this is a part of me
I wish never existed.

87
00:05:34.251 --> 00:05:36.354
And as of tomorrow.

88
00:05:36.378 --> 00:05:37.897
it no longer does.

89
00:05:37.921 --> 00:05:40.191
I'm leaving town. Starting over.

90
00:05:40.215 --> 00:05:41.467
As Ben Reilly.

91
00:05:43.844 --> 00:05:45.655
I'm sorry. Freckles. I...

92
00:05:45.679 --> 00:05:47.699
I wish I could offer you the same chance.

93
00:05:47.723 --> 00:05:49.701
That's it?

94
00:05:49.725 --> 00:05:52.370
I-I-I can't change your mind?

95
00:05:52.394 --> 00:05:54.021
Been a long time coming.

96
00:05:55.522 --> 00:05:57.900
I-I wish it didn't have to be this way.

97
00:06:02.780 --> 00:06:04.113
What did you...

98
00:08:45.442 --> 00:08:47.545
There we are.

99
00:08:47.569 --> 00:08:49.047
Stay calm. Mr. Reilly.

100
00:08:49.071 --> 00:08:50.882
Deep breaths.

101
00:08:50.906 --> 00:08:54.177
Took quite a lot of secobarbital
to keep you sedated.

102
00:08:54.201 --> 00:08:56.262
I'm sure you must feel pretty rotten.

103
00:08:56.286 --> 00:08:58.223
Wh-Where am I?

104
00:08:58.247 --> 00:09:00.457
My private laboratory.

105
00:09:01.917 --> 00:09:03.728
Wh-What is this? Why am I.

106
00:09:03.752 --> 00:09:06.147
Everything's okay. Mr. Reilly.

107
00:09:06.171 --> 00:09:08.608
I just need to run some preliminary tests.

108
00:09:08.632 --> 00:09:10.944
Investigations into your blood makeup.

109
00:09:10.968 --> 00:09:13.112
your proteins. your genetic material.

110
00:09:13.136 --> 00:09:14.137
Uncuff me.

111
00:09:14.721 --> 00:09:17.492
Trust me. this will all be a lot easier

112
00:09:17.516 --> 00:09:19.494
if you calm down and let me do my work.

113
00:09:19.518 --> 00:09:20.662
Work?

114
00:09:20.686 --> 00:09:22.413
Mr. Reilly. you broke into my office

115
00:09:22.437 --> 00:09:25.333
and stole my most important files.

116
00:09:25.357 --> 00:09:26.858
Did you read the files?

117
00:09:27.484 --> 00:09:29.212
- Yes.
- Then you know who I am

118
00:09:29.236 --> 00:09:30.505
and what I'm doing.

119
00:09:30.529 --> 00:09:33.174
And I know who you are. too. Mr. Spider.

120
00:09:33.198 --> 00:09:34.717
So let's not play games.

121
00:09:34.741 --> 00:09:37.679
I have a lot of work to do
and not a lot of time to do it.

122
00:09:37.703 --> 00:09:38.763
Are we clear?

123
00:09:38.787 --> 00:09:40.848
Let me go and I won't kill you.

124
00:09:40.872 --> 00:09:44.102
No. Threats like that are why we need
to keep you restrained.

125
00:09:44.126 --> 00:09:46.271
It's not a threat. it's a promise.

126
00:09:46.295 --> 00:09:48.398
You're very convincing.

127
00:09:48.422 --> 00:09:50.316
But we know what type of man
you really are.

128
00:09:50.340 --> 00:09:52.986
You ran into danger

129
00:09:53.010 --> 00:09:55.613
to liberate a camp of tortured soldiers.

130
00:09:55.637 --> 00:09:57.782
You saved Ogden's life.

131
00:09:57.806 --> 00:10:00.285
- Yes.
- And then you came home

132
00:10:00.309 --> 00:10:02.078
and chose to save a lot more.

133
00:10:02.102 --> 00:10:04.687
You're not a murderer. You're a hero.

134
00:10:08.483 --> 00:10:09.752
You'll never break those.

135
00:10:09.776 --> 00:10:12.755
We have enough drugs in you
to weaken King Kong.

136
00:10:12.779 --> 00:10:14.966
Now I'm simply going to draw some blood.

137
00:10:14.990 --> 00:10:16.658
A child can sit through this.

138
00:10:17.159 --> 00:10:19.786
Ogden. prep the blood draw
and retrieval kits.

139
00:10:21.371 --> 00:10:23.474
This won't do you any good.

140
00:10:23.498 --> 00:10:25.292
I've been here before.

141
00:10:27.002 --> 00:10:28.670
<i>Jones! Jones!</i>

142
00:12:15.902 --> 00:12:17.445
At ease. Soldier.

143
00:12:19.114 --> 00:12:20.906
Sit. Sit.

144
00:12:23.493 --> 00:12:24.887
You okay?

145
00:12:24.911 --> 00:12:26.389
In a fair amount of pain. I hear.

146
00:12:26.413 --> 00:12:29.392
- Nothing...
- I can't... handle. sir.

147
00:12:29.416 --> 00:12:30.810
Glad to hear it.

148
00:12:30.834 --> 00:12:33.396
The most important thing
is to get you comfortable.

149
00:12:33.420 --> 00:12:36.149
The good news is you've got the finest
medical team in the whole world

150
00:12:36.173 --> 00:12:38.526
all 100% focused on you.

151
00:12:38.550 --> 00:12:40.278
You can't beat that. can you?

152
00:12:40.302 --> 00:12:42.738
No. sir.

153
00:12:42.762 --> 00:12:44.240
Get him a pop.

154
00:12:44.264 --> 00:12:45.950
Chocolate bar. Anything he needs. okay?

155
00:12:45.974 --> 00:12:47.475
- Yes. sir.
- What...

156
00:12:49.186 --> 00:12:51.771
What is happening... to me... sir?

157
00:12:53.190 --> 00:12:55.668
I think we're all wondering that.

158
00:12:55.692 --> 00:12:58.195
But we'll get to the bottom of it.
don't you worry.

159
00:13:00.030 --> 00:13:01.674
They cut me open.

160
00:13:01.698 --> 00:13:03.217
pulled me apart.

161
00:13:03.241 --> 00:13:04.302
put me back together.

162
00:13:04.326 --> 00:13:05.678
They didn't learn a thing.

163
00:13:05.702 --> 00:13:08.514
I know every detail
of the Army's examination.

164
00:13:08.538 --> 00:13:10.725
I have studied their findings exhaustively.

165
00:13:10.749 --> 00:13:12.518
But that was a long time ago.

166
00:13:12.542 --> 00:13:15.146
The science has advanced
by leaps and bounds.

167
00:13:15.170 --> 00:13:16.254
You're one of 'em.

168
00:13:16.838 --> 00:13:18.816
Don't you dare

169
00:13:18.840 --> 00:13:20.776
confuse me with them.

170
00:13:20.800 --> 00:13:23.404
Those scientists only cared about war.

171
00:13:23.428 --> 00:13:25.406
They took one look at you.

172
00:13:25.430 --> 00:13:26.532
and they were just like the Germans.

173
00:13:26.556 --> 00:13:28.826
They wanted to use you as weapons.

174
00:13:28.850 --> 00:13:31.393
I am trying to do the opposite.

175
00:13:32.479 --> 00:13:34.332
This...

176
00:13:34.356 --> 00:13:35.440
is personal.

177
00:13:36.107 --> 00:13:37.108
Yes.

178
00:13:37.692 --> 00:13:39.194
You lost someone.

179
00:13:40.654 --> 00:13:41.821
My son.

180
00:13:42.405 --> 00:13:44.282
Have you ever lost someone. Mr. Reilly?

181
00:13:45.283 --> 00:13:49.430
Someone so close to you that
it felt like a part of you was gone. too?

182
00:13:49.454 --> 00:13:50.556
Yes.

183
00:13:50.580 --> 00:13:53.392
Well. what if you could have done
something about it?

184
00:13:53.416 --> 00:13:55.520
What if you knew that you were losing them

185
00:13:55.544 --> 00:13:58.397
but that the power to change that.

186
00:13:58.421 --> 00:14:01.174
to save them. lay in your hands?

187
00:14:01.841 --> 00:14:03.510
Wouldn't you do it?

188
00:14:04.094 --> 00:14:06.929
Wouldn't you try everything?

189
00:14:21.278 --> 00:14:24.072
You can't bring your loved one back.
Mr. Reilly. but I can.

190
00:14:24.656 --> 00:14:26.283
Is that so much to ask?

191
00:14:26.783 --> 00:14:28.678
A second chance

192
00:14:28.702 --> 00:14:29.994
for my son?

193
00:14:39.921 --> 00:14:41.566
Now you understand.

194
00:14:41.590 --> 00:14:43.192
There's nothing I won't do

195
00:14:43.216 --> 00:14:44.426
to keep him alive.

196
00:14:45.427 --> 00:14:48.554
Your friend and I have that in common.

197
00:14:49.723 --> 00:14:51.200
- My friend?
- The woman

198
00:14:51.224 --> 00:14:52.660
who told me how to find you.

199
00:14:52.684 --> 00:14:55.811
She also has someone
that she is desperate to save.

200
00:14:59.316 --> 00:15:01.776
- Cat.
- She's quite beautiful.

201
00:15:02.944 --> 00:15:04.589
And determined.

202
00:15:04.613 --> 00:15:06.215
I'm...

203
00:15:06.239 --> 00:15:07.490
s-scared.

204
00:15:08.533 --> 00:15:09.617
Is he okay?

205
00:15:11.077 --> 00:15:12.305
Mr. Reilly.

206
00:15:12.329 --> 00:15:14.372
- Mr. Reilly.
- It's the blood loss.

207
00:15:14.956 --> 00:15:17.667
He'll have time to recuperate
while we run the tests.

208
00:15:31.890 --> 00:15:33.117
Anything?

209
00:15:33.141 --> 00:15:35.202
Platelet counts.
erythrocytes. hemoglobin...

210
00:15:35.226 --> 00:15:38.897
His blood is utterly. completely.
maddeningly normal.

211
00:15:39.689 --> 00:15:42.084
Look. we know he's different.

212
00:15:42.108 --> 00:15:45.070
The answer is somewhere inside his body.

213
00:15:46.488 --> 00:15:47.989
We just have to find it.

214
00:16:17.227 --> 00:16:18.704
Good.

215
00:16:18.728 --> 00:16:20.456
You're awake.

216
00:16:20.480 --> 00:16:21.898
How are you feeling?

217
00:16:23.233 --> 00:16:24.960
I-I'm sorry

218
00:16:24.984 --> 00:16:26.253
about all this.

219
00:16:26.277 --> 00:16:27.487
I-I-I mean it.

220
00:16:28.154 --> 00:16:30.198
You-you gave me no option.

221
00:16:30.699 --> 00:16:32.259
Here. drink this.

222
00:16:32.283 --> 00:16:34.011
You-you-you must be thirsty.

223
00:16:34.035 --> 00:16:36.013
No. it's-it's-it's water.

224
00:16:36.037 --> 00:16:37.622
I-I-I promise.

225
00:16:46.881 --> 00:16:47.965
Wow.

226
00:16:49.426 --> 00:16:51.177
You were thirsty.

227
00:16:52.554 --> 00:16:54.323
So.

228
00:16:54.347 --> 00:16:57.201
you were just going to leave town.

229
00:16:57.225 --> 00:17:00.871
Even after I told you
that there was a chance that...

230
00:17:00.895 --> 00:17:02.832
you could save me

231
00:17:02.856 --> 00:17:04.023
and the others.

232
00:17:05.567 --> 00:17:07.485
Spider was never a hero.

233
00:17:08.486 --> 00:17:10.673
I only did it for the thrill.

234
00:17:10.697 --> 00:17:12.073
Well...

235
00:17:12.574 --> 00:17:14.868
maybe you weren't then.

236
00:17:15.785 --> 00:17:18.806
But there's still time
for you to become one.

237
00:17:18.830 --> 00:17:21.308
I'm never getting out of here alive.

238
00:17:21.332 --> 00:17:22.917
What are you talking about?

239
00:17:23.543 --> 00:17:26.355
Your mother is insane.

240
00:17:26.379 --> 00:17:27.732
No. No.

241
00:17:27.756 --> 00:17:29.108
That's not true.

242
00:17:29.132 --> 00:17:31.777
She's... just trying to save me.

243
00:17:31.801 --> 00:17:33.863
No. she's insane.

244
00:17:33.887 --> 00:17:35.656
I'm sorry to report

245
00:17:35.680 --> 00:17:37.766
that your blood samples weren't enough.

246
00:17:38.266 --> 00:17:41.537
I'm going to have to harvest
genetic material from your organs.

247
00:17:41.561 --> 00:17:44.665
Stop! If you haven't found an answer.

248
00:17:44.689 --> 00:17:46.399
it's because there isn't one.

249
00:17:46.983 --> 00:17:48.377
I will never stop.

250
00:17:48.401 --> 00:17:52.131
What kind of a mother would I be
if I didn't exhaust every option?

251
00:17:52.155 --> 00:17:54.341
There's always an answer. Mr. Reilly.

252
00:17:54.365 --> 00:17:55.968
What is that?

253
00:17:55.992 --> 00:17:57.786
What-what-what is that?

254
00:18:05.335 --> 00:18:06.795
Help me. Ogden.

255
00:18:14.385 --> 00:18:17.555
Science is about uncovering
discernible facts.

256
00:18:18.640 --> 00:18:21.035
Now. the program
that the Germans conducted altered

257
00:18:21.059 --> 00:18:23.144
their subjects' genetic makeup.

258
00:18:24.229 --> 00:18:25.873
Led to corrosion.

259
00:18:25.897 --> 00:18:27.357
decay. instability.

260
00:18:28.358 --> 00:18:33.714
For some reason. you were the only subject
who gained power without degradation.

261
00:18:33.738 --> 00:18:36.448
Where are you taking me?

262
00:18:38.952 --> 00:18:40.328
He's trying to say something.

263
00:18:43.122 --> 00:18:44.350
I like...

264
00:18:44.374 --> 00:18:45.625
ravioli.

265
00:18:46.209 --> 00:18:48.270
You will have ravioli.

266
00:18:48.294 --> 00:18:51.130
All the ravioli you want.

267
00:18:54.634 --> 00:18:58.030
I believe that whatever process
that allowed the mutation

268
00:18:58.054 --> 00:18:59.949
to stabilize within your body

269
00:18:59.973 --> 00:19:03.852
can be retrofitted
to fully cure the other mutations.

270
00:19:06.479 --> 00:19:10.191
You're going to have
a nice rest now. Mr. Reilly.

271
00:19:11.276 --> 00:19:12.694
Mask. Ogden.

272
00:19:15.196 --> 00:19:16.632
Just breathe.

273
00:19:16.656 --> 00:19:18.592
Breathe deeply.

274
00:19:18.616 --> 00:19:19.927
That's good.

275
00:19:19.951 --> 00:19:21.637
Ten.

276
00:19:21.661 --> 00:19:23.013
nine.

277
00:19:23.037 --> 00:19:24.598
eight.

278
00:19:24.622 --> 00:19:26.183
seven.

279
00:19:26.207 --> 00:19:27.291
six...

280
00:19:35.592 --> 00:19:37.444
Cut him open.

281
00:19:37.468 --> 00:19:39.095
Let's see what he's made of.

282
00:20:10.335 --> 00:20:11.770
Ruby.

283
00:20:11.794 --> 00:20:13.105
Yeah. you ding-a-ling.

284
00:20:13.129 --> 00:20:14.648
Were you expecting someone else?

285
00:20:14.672 --> 00:20:16.483
I missed you so much.

286
00:20:16.507 --> 00:20:18.068
Ruby.

287
00:20:18.092 --> 00:20:21.303
Ruby. Ruby. Ruby.

288
00:20:28.394 --> 00:20:31.356
Hey. Reilly.
Thought you could get rid of me?

289
00:20:31.940 --> 00:20:34.358
You're nothing without me.

290
00:20:58.257 --> 00:21:01.219
You son of a bitch. You set me up.

291
00:21:03.429 --> 00:21:04.823
You're a coward. Reilly.

292
00:21:04.847 --> 00:21:07.225
Fortune favors the bold.

293
00:21:07.809 --> 00:21:09.811
I tried to warn you.

294
00:21:10.603 --> 00:21:12.814
Now you're gonna burn.

295
00:22:00.403 --> 00:22:01.988
My God.

296
00:23:21.901 --> 00:23:24.296
It's time.

297
00:23:24.320 --> 00:23:26.548
Are you ready?

298
00:23:26.572 --> 00:23:27.990
Yeah.

299
00:23:30.451 --> 00:23:31.661
What's wrong?

300
00:23:33.788 --> 00:23:35.599
Are you sure this is gonna work?

301
00:23:35.623 --> 00:23:38.477
I mean. what-what if - I am as sure

302
00:23:38.501 --> 00:23:40.920
as I've ever been. All right?

303
00:23:43.548 --> 00:23:44.966
Okay.

304
00:23:46.050 --> 00:23:47.593
I'm ready.

305
00:23:48.594 --> 00:23:50.762
It's already done.

306
00:24:40.396 --> 00:24:41.748
You did it.

307
00:24:41.772 --> 00:24:43.733
You really did it.

308
00:24:45.568 --> 00:24:47.611
I cannot believe it.

309
00:24:49.280 --> 00:24:52.009
My little Freckles.

310
00:24:52.033 --> 00:24:54.261
All right.

311
00:24:54.285 --> 00:24:55.929
Robertson will have published
his story by now.

312
00:24:55.953 --> 00:24:59.892
so we-we need to clear this place out
and get out of here.

313
00:24:59.916 --> 00:25:01.334
Wh...

314
00:25:02.460 --> 00:25:04.545
We need to give Reilly the antidote first.

315
00:25:07.423 --> 00:25:08.716
We can't do that. Oggie.

316
00:25:09.342 --> 00:25:10.611
We kidnapped him.

317
00:25:10.635 --> 00:25:13.471
We operated on him against his will.

318
00:25:14.805 --> 00:25:16.700
The best thing for us.
the only hope for us

319
00:25:16.724 --> 00:25:18.619
is to just become different people.

320
00:25:18.643 --> 00:25:22.647
To disappear with no one left
who knows anything about us.

321
00:25:28.736 --> 00:25:29.903
What are you saying?

322
00:25:33.741 --> 00:25:34.867
No.

323
00:25:35.451 --> 00:25:37.054
They will throw us both in prison.

324
00:25:37.078 --> 00:25:40.682
I have not spent
the last 15 years of my life

325
00:25:40.706 --> 00:25:42.267
trying to give you your life back

326
00:25:42.291 --> 00:25:45.312
just to have you waste away in a jail cell.

327
00:25:45.336 --> 00:25:47.648
I'm sorry. Ogden.

328
00:25:47.672 --> 00:25:51.092
His life was always the price of yours.

329
00:25:58.349 --> 00:26:00.244
I'll do it.

330
00:26:00.268 --> 00:26:03.872
- Ogden.
- After everything we've both been through.

331
00:26:03.896 --> 00:26:08.651
I need to look him in the eye.
soldier-to-soldier.

332
00:26:10.736 --> 00:26:12.279
Okay.

333
00:26:34.468 --> 00:26:37.096
I feel like a young boy
on a Christmas morning.

334
00:26:38.180 --> 00:26:41.868
If this doctor can give us the name
of every superpowered man from that camp.

335
00:26:41.892 --> 00:26:44.145
we'll have an army nobody can stop.

336
00:26:44.729 --> 00:26:47.374
Not even the goddamn Spider.

337
00:26:47.398 --> 00:26:50.026
The suffering they put you through...

338
00:26:51.444 --> 00:26:53.070
they'll rue the day.

339
00:28:02.515 --> 00:28:03.808
Don't.

340
00:28:09.605 --> 00:28:11.500
Ogden?

341
00:28:11.524 --> 00:28:13.085
You were right.

342
00:28:13.109 --> 00:28:15.027
She sent me to kill you.

343
00:28:15.611 --> 00:28:17.464
But you saved my life.

344
00:28:17.488 --> 00:28:19.656
Least I can do is try to save yours.

345
00:28:21.242 --> 00:28:24.537
Just promise me you won't hurt her.

346
00:28:25.538 --> 00:28:27.682
Yeah. I'm not the one with the gun.

347
00:28:27.706 --> 00:28:29.893
I'm not the one with the spider powers.

348
00:28:29.917 --> 00:28:34.422
I'm just trying to get home.

349
00:28:37.716 --> 00:28:39.175
Let's get you home.

350
00:29:01.991 --> 00:29:04.702
These doors are getting bigger and bigger.

351
00:29:20.885 --> 00:29:22.237
Wow.

352
00:29:22.261 --> 00:29:24.406
Look at you.

353
00:29:24.430 --> 00:29:26.158
Marvelous. Just marvelous.

354
00:29:26.182 --> 00:29:27.701
You're back.

355
00:29:27.725 --> 00:29:29.286
What are your plans?

356
00:29:29.310 --> 00:29:30.495
Pardon me?

357
00:29:30.519 --> 00:29:32.205
Well. now that you've got your life back.

358
00:29:32.229 --> 00:29:35.375
what are you planning
on doing with it. Freckles?

359
00:29:35.399 --> 00:29:37.919
I don't know...

360
00:29:37.943 --> 00:29:39.629
I...

361
00:29:39.653 --> 00:29:41.590
I've been preparing to die for so long.

362
00:29:41.614 --> 00:29:43.800
I never really thought about how to live.

363
00:29:43.824 --> 00:29:45.302
Are you. are you okay?

364
00:29:45.326 --> 00:29:46.720
What day is it?

365
00:29:46.744 --> 00:29:48.263
- Excuse me?
- The day. the day.

366
00:29:48.287 --> 00:29:49.764
What's today?

367
00:29:49.788 --> 00:29:51.892
Monday. M-Monday afternoon.

368
00:29:51.916 --> 00:29:53.351
Poo.

369
00:29:53.375 --> 00:29:55.187
Robbie's chasing his Pulitzer.

370
00:29:55.211 --> 00:29:56.855
He's published the location of the lab.

371
00:29:56.879 --> 00:29:58.463
They'll be here any second.

372
00:30:04.512 --> 00:30:06.281
How many do you think there are?

373
00:30:06.305 --> 00:30:07.699
Hard to say.

374
00:30:07.723 --> 00:30:09.117
There were dozens of us at the camp.

375
00:30:09.141 --> 00:30:12.496
Imagine a lot
made their way back to New York.

376
00:30:12.520 --> 00:30:16.357
Anybody had any trouble over the years
would've found their way to Faber.

377
00:30:40.005 --> 00:30:41.191
You okay?

378
00:30:41.215 --> 00:30:43.216
What's it look like? I'm fine.

379
00:30:44.802 --> 00:30:46.971
Cherry red. My favorite.

380
00:30:52.059 --> 00:30:54.395
It's up and through there.

381
00:30:57.565 --> 00:30:58.774
You're not coming?

382
00:31:00.526 --> 00:31:01.818
I'm not leaving her.

383
00:31:02.987 --> 00:31:04.822
You can't beat those guys.

384
00:31:05.406 --> 00:31:06.949
You're probably right.

385
00:31:09.410 --> 00:31:11.036
But she's my mom.

386
00:31:34.059 --> 00:31:35.269
Up you get.

387
00:31:36.520 --> 00:31:38.498
What's the matter. Doc?

388
00:31:38.522 --> 00:31:40.292
You don't look that thrilled to see us.

389
00:31:40.316 --> 00:31:41.918
I'm sorry. I'm-I'm just surprised.

390
00:31:41.942 --> 00:31:43.336
'Cause your secret lab's

391
00:31:43.360 --> 00:31:44.862
not a secret no more?

392
00:31:45.946 --> 00:31:47.382
So. we're monsters.

393
00:31:47.406 --> 00:31:48.883
are we?

394
00:31:48.907 --> 00:31:50.802
Quite the operation you've got

395
00:31:50.826 --> 00:31:52.220
going down here.

396
00:31:52.244 --> 00:31:55.181
Everything but a cauldron
and two weird sisters.

397
00:31:55.205 --> 00:31:56.474
That story says you did this to us.

398
00:31:56.498 --> 00:32:00.145
No. absolutely not. Quite the opposite.

399
00:32:00.169 --> 00:32:01.855
- Liar. liar.
- All right.

400
00:32:01.879 --> 00:32:04.214
Hold your horses. Everybody.

401
00:32:05.716 --> 00:32:08.695
Now we'll all have a conversation.

402
00:32:08.719 --> 00:32:10.196
Nice and civilized.

403
00:32:10.220 --> 00:32:11.781
- Right. Doc?
- Of course.

404
00:32:11.805 --> 00:32:14.034
Very pleased
to make your acquaintance. Doctor.

405
00:32:14.058 --> 00:32:16.161
- Do you know who I am?
- Yes.

406
00:32:16.185 --> 00:32:18.872
Good. Now tell the boys
you're not in the business

407
00:32:18.896 --> 00:32:20.874
- of making monsters.
- No.

408
00:32:20.898 --> 00:32:24.336
No. All I have ever tried to do
is to help you all.

409
00:32:24.360 --> 00:32:27.047
- Every one of you.
- Hey. how is old Oggie?

410
00:32:27.071 --> 00:32:29.405
He finally kick
the proverbial bucket or what?

411
00:32:30.532 --> 00:32:32.052
Sadly. yes.

412
00:32:32.076 --> 00:32:35.680
Now. my friends here
say you've been treating

413
00:32:35.704 --> 00:32:37.265
their various maladies.

414
00:32:37.289 --> 00:32:42.086
I'm curious to know
if there are others like them.

415
00:32:43.170 --> 00:32:45.023
Yes.

416
00:32:45.047 --> 00:32:47.275
I could take you to them now.

417
00:32:47.299 --> 00:32:50.654
They're here? Even better.

418
00:32:50.678 --> 00:32:52.638
Lead on. my dear.

419
00:33:49.862 --> 00:33:51.280
My God.

420
00:34:04.168 --> 00:34:05.711
What is all this?

421
00:34:07.129 --> 00:34:09.399
- They're all dead?
- I did my best.

422
00:34:09.423 --> 00:34:11.151
but they succumbed to their mutations

423
00:34:11.175 --> 00:34:13.236
before I'd figured out a way to save them.

424
00:34:13.260 --> 00:34:15.572
And then you put them in jars
like a bunch of freaks?

425
00:34:15.596 --> 00:34:17.848
No. that is - It's Johnny.

426
00:34:20.225 --> 00:34:21.852
Johnny Forte.

427
00:34:50.672 --> 00:34:52.233
You never cared about us.

428
00:34:52.257 --> 00:34:53.735
That is not true.

429
00:34:53.759 --> 00:34:55.779
You know what it's been like?
Living like this?

430
00:34:55.803 --> 00:34:57.447
- Please...
- Our bodies somehow stronger

431
00:34:57.471 --> 00:34:58.656
and weaker at the same time?

432
00:34:58.680 --> 00:35:00.700
- The world calling us monsters.
- Please listen.

433
00:35:00.724 --> 00:35:04.078
I have finally figured it out.

434
00:35:04.102 --> 00:35:07.832
I promise you I can help you all.
if you will just let me.

435
00:35:07.856 --> 00:35:09.876
Help us?

436
00:35:09.900 --> 00:35:11.276
You mean like you helped them?

437
00:35:12.361 --> 00:35:14.672
These men was our comrades.

438
00:35:14.696 --> 00:35:16.216
Our brothers.

439
00:35:16.240 --> 00:35:18.635
We fought with these men.

440
00:35:18.659 --> 00:35:21.161
We suffered with these men.

441
00:35:33.966 --> 00:35:35.652
Wait.

442
00:35:35.676 --> 00:35:37.093
Wait. I know you.

443
00:35:38.595 --> 00:35:40.305
We were in the cell together.

444
00:35:41.431 --> 00:35:43.451
I grabbed the guard.

445
00:35:43.475 --> 00:35:44.893
you put the knife in.

446
00:35:47.855 --> 00:35:49.940
Nobody shoots me. you little bastard.

447
00:35:52.442 --> 00:35:54.152
Dirk. stop! What are you doing?

448
00:35:56.446 --> 00:35:58.240
Get off of me.

449
00:36:09.877 --> 00:36:11.229
There's nothing here for us.

450
00:36:11.253 --> 00:36:12.671
Let's go.

451
00:36:16.049 --> 00:36:20.553
You're going to have to learn
some impulse control. son.

452
00:36:31.106 --> 00:36:32.333
Hey.

453
00:36:32.357 --> 00:36:35.420
- You got shit in your teeth.
- No.

454
00:36:35.444 --> 00:36:37.088
- I look so dumb.
- Yeah. you look real stupid.

455
00:36:37.112 --> 00:36:39.257
I was in the car
with those guys for an hour.

456
00:36:39.281 --> 00:36:40.967
- Now. don't bite my finger.
- You think they saw?

457
00:36:40.991 --> 00:36:43.303
Yeah. Right back here.

458
00:36:43.327 --> 00:36:45.305
- Yeah.
- Did you get it?

459
00:36:45.329 --> 00:36:47.181
You know. I wanted
to be a dentist when I was a kid.

460
00:36:47.205 --> 00:36:48.873
- Yeah?
- Yeah. I got it.

461
00:36:50.042 --> 00:36:53.085
God! The hell was that?
